msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/name"
msgid "Dynamo"
msgstr "Dinamo"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/name_big"
msgid "Dynamo"
msgstr "Dinamo"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/story"
msgid ""
"Ever since the Germans broke through at Sedan three weeks ago, the Allies "
"have been on the back foot.\n"
"\n"
"Calais fell on the 27th, and Belgium capitulated on the 28th. The perimeter "
"around Dunkirk is shrinking, and an attack on the remaining allied forces "
"seems to be a matter of time only.\n"
"\n"
"The Germans are pushing in on the shrinking perimeter from all sides, "
"including from the air.\n"
"\n"
"Today, it’s up to you and your comrades to buy the evacuation operation more "
"time and to keep the Germans away from the beach as far as possible."
msgstr ""
"Desde que los alemanes rompieron las líneas enemigas en Sedán hace tres "
"semanas, los aliados se han visto obligados a retroceder. Calais cayó el día "
"27 y Bélgica se rindió el 28. El perímetro alrededor de Dunkerque se está "
"reduciendo y el ataque contra las fuerzas aliadas restantes parece ser solo "
"cuestión de tiempo.\n"
"\n"
"Los alemanes están presionando el perímetro cada vez más reducido desde "
"todos los flancos, incluso desde el aire. Hoy, depende de ti y de tus "
"compañeros ganar tiempo para la operación de evacuación y mantener a los "
"alemanes lo más lejos posible de la playa."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/date"
msgid "June 3rd, 1940 · Dunkirk, France"
msgstr "3 de junio de 1940 · Dunkerque, Francia"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/place"
msgid "British Expeditionary Force, Armée de Terre"
msgstr "Fuerza Expedicionaria Británica, Ejército de Tierra"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/outro_completed"
msgid ""
"Your tenacity and courage have saved many lives today. The British empire "
"will be able to continue the fight another day as the last country in Europe "
"fighting against Germany."
msgstr ""
"Tu tenacidad y valentía han salvado muchas vidas hoy. El Imperio Británico "
"podrá continuar la lucha un día más como el último país de Europa que lucha "
"contra Alemania."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/outro_failed"
msgid ""
"Operation Dynamo has not been very successful, and it remains to be seen "
"whether we will stay in the war - or surrender."
msgstr ""
"La Operación Dinamo no ha tenido mucho éxito, y aún está por ver si "
"continuaremos en la guerra o nos rendiremos."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/cutscene/intro_01"
msgid ""
"With all due respect, Sir, but you only won because Cliff Bastin was out "
"half the season."
msgstr ""
"Con todo respeto, señor, pero solo ganaste porque Cliff Bastin estuvo fuera "
"la mitad de la temporada."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/cutscene/intro_02"
msgid "Keep telling yourself that. Everton didn’t need Bastin to lift the cup."
msgstr ""
"Sigue diciéndote eso. El Everton no necesitó a Bastin para levantar la copa."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/cutscene/intro_03"
msgid ""
"Lawton just had one flashy season. He’d never last against Arsenal’s back "
"line in their prime!"
msgstr ""
"Lawton solo tuvo una temporada brillante. ¡Nunca aguantarías contra la "
"defensa del Arsenal en su mejor momento!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/cutscene/intro_04"
msgid ""
"We have more of these flyers than we do toilet paper… They really want us to "
"wave the white flag."
msgstr ""
"Tenemos más folletos de estos que papel higiénico... Realmente quieren que "
"ondeemos la bandera blanca."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/cutscene/intro_05"
msgid "God help us if Jerry gets his hands on us…"
msgstr "Que Dios nos ayude si Jerry nos pone las manos encima..."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/cutscene/intro_06"
msgid "Let’s just… Let’s just keep moving…"
msgstr "Vamos... Sigamos adelante..."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/cutscene/intro_07"
msgid "Sir… Haven’t you heard what they do to prisoners?"
msgstr "Señor... ¿No has oído lo que les hacen a los prisioneros?"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/cutscene/intro_08"
msgid "I’ve only heard the rumors, same as you."
msgstr "Solo he oído rumores, igual que tú."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/cutscene/intro_10"
msgid "Is it true they use prisoners as bloody human shields?"
msgstr "¿Es cierto que usan a los presos como escudos humanos?"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/cutscene/intro_11"
msgid ""
"Where did you hear that, Corporal? Same place you heard the Gunners were "
"still the best in England?"
msgstr ""
"¿Dónde has oído eso, cabo? ¿En el mismo sitio donde oíste que ese equipo "
"seguía siendo los mejores de Inglaterra?"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/cutscene/intro_12"
msgid ""
"The whole company is talking about this. And there's worse… Have you heard "
"what the French are saying?"
msgstr ""
"Toda la empresa está hablando de esto. Y hay algo peor... ¿Has oído lo que "
"dicen los franceses?"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/cutscene/intro_13"
msgid "Alright, Corporal, let’s just hope we don’t find out."
msgstr "Muy bien, cabo, esperemos que no lo descubramos."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/cutscene/intro_14"
msgid "Oh my God…"
msgstr "Dios mío..."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/cutscene/intro_15"
msgid "They’ve sent civilian boats? Well, I reckon it’s better than nothing."
msgstr "¿Han enviado barcos civiles? Bueno, supongo que es mejor que nada."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/cutscene/intro_16"
msgid "There you are, lieutenant! Over here, I’ve got a job for you."
msgstr "¡Ahí estás, teniente! Por aquí, tengo un trabajo para ti."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/part01_01"
msgid ""
"Set up the first line of defense at the double. Our engineers are busy "
"sabotaging the vehicles to prevent them from falling into enemy hands. We "
"have to hold the Germans here until they are done."
msgstr ""
"Estableced la primera línea de defensa rápidamente. Nuestros ingenieros "
"están ocupados saboteando los vehículos para evitar que caigan en manos "
"enemigas. Tenemos que contener a los alemanes aquí hasta que terminen."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/part01_02"
msgid ""
"Calling this situation critical is an understatement. The evacuation is far "
"from complete and the enemy may strike any second."
msgstr ""
"Calificar esta situación de crítica es quedarse corto. La evacuación está "
"lejos de completarse y el enemigo puede atacar en cualquier momento."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/part01_03"
msgid ""
"During the retreat we left a lot of weapons and ammunition in these crates. "
"Take a look inside them."
msgstr ""
"Durante la retirada dejamos muchas armas y municiones en estas cajas. Echad "
"un vistazo dentro."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/part01_04"
msgid "Sir, where are the rest of the gun crews?"
msgstr "Señor, ¿dónde está el resto de la tripulación de artillería?"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/part01_05"
msgid "I beg your pardon, Lieutenant?"
msgstr "¿Perdón, teniente?"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/part01_06"
msgid ""
"We have a couple of AT guns but… Not enough trained personnel to operate "
"them."
msgstr ""
"Tenemos un par de cañones antitanque, pero... no hay suficiente personal "
"capacitado para manejarlos."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/part01_07"
msgid ""
"They’re most likely either on the beach or on their way home. I’m afraid "
"some of your riflemen have to learn on the fly. This evacuation has been a "
"total mess from the beginning."
msgstr ""
"Lo más probable es que estén en la playa o de camino a casa. Me temo que "
"algunos de tus fusileros tendrán que aprender sobre la marcha. Esta "
"evacuación ha sido un desastre total desde el principio."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/part01_11"
msgid "What the?.. Jerry is already here!"
msgstr "¿Qué...? ¡Los boches ya están aquí!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/part01_12"
msgid ""
"Damn, I’ve seen this before. It looks like they’re probing our line, that "
"means the fun is about to begin…"
msgstr ""
"Maldición, ya he visto esto antes. Parece que están probando nuestras "
"líneas, lo que significa que la diversión está a punto de comenzar..."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/part01_14"
msgid "Watch out, enemy plane incoming! Get to cover!"
msgstr "¡Cuidado, se acerca un avión enemigo! ¡Ponte a cubierto!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/part01_15"
msgid "We don’t have much time, bolster the line as much as you can."
msgstr "No tenemos mucho tiempo, refuerza la línea tanto como puedas."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/part01_16"
msgid ""
"Sir, with all due respect… How are we meant to hold here? We’re already "
"running low."
msgstr ""
"Señor, con todo respeto... ¿Cómo se supone que vamos a aguantar aquí? Ya nos "
"estamos quedando sin provisiones."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/part01_17"
msgid ""
"I saw some crates with small arms ammunition that were left during the "
"retreat. Take a look at them."
msgstr ""
"Vi algunas cajas con munición para armas pequeñas que quedaron durante la "
"retirada. Échales un vistazo."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/part02_01"
msgid "Here they are! Hold fast!"
msgstr "¡Aquí están! ¡Agarraos fuerte!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/part02_02"
msgid ""
"The engineers are still working on the vehicles. Use anything you can find "
"in ammunition crates and don’t let them get too close to us!"
msgstr ""
"Los ingenieros siguen trabajando en los vehículos. ¡Utiliza todo lo que "
"encuentres en las cajas de municiones y no dejes que se acerquen demasiado a "
"nosotros!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/part02_03"
msgid "Damn, we haven’t got enough AT-guns to stop all these tanks…"
msgstr ""
"Maldición, no tenemos suficientes cañones antitanque para detener a todos "
"estos tanques..."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/part02_04"
msgid ""
"The retreating forces have left us a lot of rifles with cup dischargers. "
"Their AT grenades are powerful enough to stop a tank at close quarters. We "
"can shoot from behind fences and from buildings to ambush their vehicles."
msgstr ""
"Las fuerzas en retirada nos han dejado muchos rifles con descargadores de "
"copa. Sus granadas antitanque son lo suficientemente potentes como para "
"detener un tanque a corta distancia. Podemos disparar desde detrás de vallas "
"y edificios para tender emboscadas a sus vehículos."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/part02_06"
msgid ""
"The boys have finished! Lieutenant Shaw, retreat to the second line, I’m "
"going to put the remainder of one of my companies under your command."
msgstr ""
"¡Los chicos han terminado! Teniente Shaw, retírate a la segunda línea, voy a "
"poner el resto de una de mis compañías bajo tu mando."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/part02_07"
msgid ""
"The engineers have set up a timer to blow up the vehicles. Make sure you "
"stay well clear of them!"
msgstr ""
"Los ingenieros han programado un temporizador para hacer explotar los "
"vehículos. ¡Asegúrate de mantenerte alejado de ellos!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/part02_08"
msgid "The vehicles are going to go up any second. Be careful."
msgstr "Los vehículos van a subir en cualquier momento. Ten cuidado."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/part02_09"
msgid "What a waste. But I reckon it’s better than leaving them to the enemy."
msgstr ""
"Qué desperdicio. Pero supongo que es mejor que dejarlos en manos del enemigo."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/part02_lost"
msgid ""
"Our defense has collapsed! Lieutenant Shaw, I am relieving you of your "
"command, dismissed!"
msgstr ""
"¡Nuestra defensa se ha derrumbado! Teniente Shaw, te relevo de tu mando, "
"¡puedes retirarte!"

msgctxt ""
"mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/part02_fallback_reminder"
msgid "Fall back to the second line, lieutenant! Think of your men."
msgstr "¡Retirada a la segunda línea, teniente! Piensa en tus hombres."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/dogfight_01"
msgid "Watch the skies, incoming enemy planes!"
msgstr "¡Mirad al cielo, se acercan aviones enemigos!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/dogfight_02"
msgid "Hey, look! The Brylcreem Boys decided to show up! Go get ‘em!"
msgstr "¡Eh, mirad! ¡Los Brylcreem Boys han decidido aparecer! ¡A por ellos!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/dogfight_03"
msgid ""
"We should assist them somehow… Has anyone seen a functional anti-air gun?"
msgstr ""
"Deberíamos ayudaros de alguna manera... ¿Alguien ha visto algún cañón "
"antiaéreo que funcione?"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/dogfight_04"
msgid ""
"I am afraid all of them are out of service. With a bit of luck you might "
"repair one of them."
msgstr ""
"Me temo que todos están fuera de servicio. Con un poco de suerte, quizá "
"puedas reparar alguno."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/dogfight_05"
msgid ""
"Excellent, that’s exactly what we need right now. This Bofors can shoot the "
"bloody planes down."
msgstr ""
"Excelente, eso es justo lo que necesitamos ahora mismo. Este Bofors puede "
"derribar a esos malditos aviones."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/dogfight_06"
msgid "More German planes incoming, reload the gun!"
msgstr "¡Se acercan más aviones alemanes, recarga el arma!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/dogfight_07"
msgid "I don’t see anymore of them. Brilliant work! I bet the RAF will owe us."
msgstr ""
"Ya no veo a ninguno. ¡Excelente trabajo! Apuesto a que la RAF nos deberá un "
"favor."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/dogfight_08"
msgid "Well, at least we’ve repaired this Bofors."
msgstr "Bueno, al menos hemos reparado este Bofors."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/dogfight_09"
msgid ""
"They just shot down one of our planes! We need to find something against "
"these German fighters!"
msgstr ""
"¡Acaban de derribar uno de nuestros aviones! ¡Tenemos que encontrar algo "
"contra estos cazas alemanes!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/dogfight_10"
msgid "They’ve destroyed our fighters! We can’t count on RAF support anymore."
msgstr ""
"¡Han destruido vuestros cazas! Ya no podemos contar con el apoyo de la RAF."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/pl_reinf_01"
msgid ""
"Sir, there are a few allied troops coming from the east! Where are they "
"coming from?"
msgstr "¡Señor, hay unas tropas aliadas que vienen del este! ¿De dónde vienen?"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/pl_reinf_02"
msgid ""
"These are the reinforcements we expected an hour ago… Use them to fill any "
"gaps in your line."
msgstr ""
"Estos son los refuerzos que esperábamos hace una hora... Úsalos para cubrir "
"cualquier hueco en tu línea."

msgctxt ""
"mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/"
"pl_first_line_retreat_warning"
msgid "Where the hell are you going?! There was no order for falling back!"
msgstr "¿¡A dónde demonios vas?! ¡No se ha dado ninguna orden de retirada!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/evac_boat_01"
msgid ""
"Vessels from home are beginning to arrive. We must hold our ground to "
"protect the evacuation."
msgstr ""
"Los barcos de casa están empezando a llegar. Debemos mantener nuestras "
"posiciones para proteger la evacuación."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/evac_boat_02"
msgid "There’s a vessel at the mole, steady on!"
msgstr "Hay un barco en el muelle, ¡mantén el rumbo!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/evac_boat_03"
msgid "Another boat is at the mole, provide cover!"
msgstr "Hay otro barco en el muelle, ¡proporciona cobertura!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/evac_boat_04"
msgid "A transport is at the mole, keep at it!"
msgstr "Hay un transporte en el muelle, ¡sigue así!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/evac_boat_05"
msgid ""
"This is the last one! We must hold a little longer while the wounded are "
"loaded."
msgstr ""
"¡Este es el último! Tenemos que aguantar un poco más mientras suben a los "
"heridos."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/enemy_near_beach"
msgid ""
"The Germans have reached the beach! Wipe them out before they slaughter our "
"men at the mole!"
msgstr ""
"¡Los alemanes han llegado a la playa! ¡Acabad con ellos antes de que "
"masacren a nuestros hombres en el muelle!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/cutscene/outro_01"
msgid "To the mole, quick!"
msgstr "¡Al suelo, rápido!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/cutscene/outro_02"
msgid "Damn, how many of you are still out there…"
msgstr "Maldita sea, ¿cuántos de ustedes siguen ahí fuera?"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/cutscene/outro_03"
msgid "Major! Greenwood, have you seen him?"
msgstr "¡Comandante! Greenwood, ¿lo has visto?"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/cutscene/outro_04"
msgid "We’re the last ones! Move your arse to the mole, lieutenant!"
msgstr "¡Somos los últimos! ¡Mueve el culo, teniente!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/cutscene/outro_05"
msgid "Shit…"
msgstr "Mierda..."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/narrator/cutscene/outro_06"
msgid "I don’t know how we made it out of there…"
msgstr "No sé cómo logramos salir de allí..."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/ui/gameover_early_retreat"
msgid ""
"You fell back too early. Do not send your units too far from your first "
"defensive line."
msgstr ""
"Te has replegado demasiado pronto. No envíes tus unidades demasiado lejos de "
"tu primera línea defensiva."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/ui/gameover_def_lost"
msgid "The enemy has broken through."
msgstr "El enemigo ha cruzado."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/ui/progress_evac"
msgid "You have saved %1% lives"
msgstr "Has salvado %1% vidas."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/ui/reinf_airstrike"
msgid "Air Strike"
msgstr "Ataque aéreo"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/ui/timer_preparation"
msgid "Prepare your defensive lines"
msgstr "Prepara tus líneas defensivas."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/ui/timer_sabotage"
msgid "Vehicles sabotage, stay away"
msgstr "Sabotaje a vehículos, mantente alejado."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/ui/hint_airstrike"
msgid ""
"Royal Air Forces are ready to provide close air support. There are only "
"<c(B29557)>2 planes available</c>, use them as a last resort."
msgstr ""
"Las Royal Air Force está lista para proporcionar apoyo aéreo cercano. Solo "
"hay dos aviones disponibles <c(B29557)>2</c>, utilízalos como último recurso."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/ui/timer_early_fallback"
msgid "<c(B29557)>Bring your units back to the first defensive line</c>"
msgstr ""
"<c(B29557)>Lleva tus unidades de vuelta a la primera línea defensiva.</c>"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/tasks/01_defense"
msgid "Protect the Evactuation of British Expeditionary Forces"
msgstr "Proteger la evacuación de las fuerzas expedicionarias británicas."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/tasks/02_line_one"
msgid "Hold the First Line while Engineers are sabotaging Abandoned Vehicles"
msgstr ""
"Mantén la primera línea mientras los ingenieros sabotean los vehículos "
"abandonados."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/tasks/03_fallback"
msgid "Fall back to the Second Line"
msgstr "Retrocede a la segunda línea."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/tasks/04_line_two"
msgid "Slow down the German advance"
msgstr "Frenar el avance alemán"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/tasks/opt03_dogfight"
msgid "Help the Royal Air Force to win the Dogfight"
msgstr "Ayuda a la Royal Air Force a ganar el combate aéreo."

msgctxt ""
"mission/single/05-eng/1940_06_03_dunkirk/tasks/opt03_dogfight_completed"
msgid "Unlike Tom - Help the Royal Air Force to win the Dogfight"
msgstr ""
"A diferencia de Tom: ayuda a la Royal Air Force a ganar el combate aéreo."
